Pocky Is God wrote:Saint wrote:Quirinus wrote:Saint wrote:I truly resent take your kids to work day because it's basically annoying/bothering people who don't have kids for the sake of those that do, without any form of alternative for the child-less. If I'm friends with my co-workers, I already know their kids. If I'm not, I don't care.Whatever. From my experience, the kids are never that bad. However, IMO, I don't like take your kids to work day because most workplaces aren't really that interesting to kids nor are they usually equipped to handle kids for longer than an hour, at best. I feel bad for the kids.It's not so much the kids acting badly as much as they're basically giving a benefit to the parents without giving the childless people anything.So this is a grown up version of "Awwwww they got something so I want something too!"Yes, but you don't have to be a dick about it. I get where Saint is coming from. It's part of modern western society that we give extra benefits to parents, and those that are childless have to pick up the extra slack, whether it's having to cover more hours/efforts at work, or paying more in taxes (I'm a single person with a decent salary. I get no tax breaks. Zero. None. Nada. I pay more in taxes that some entire families, and I'm not rich, just your average middle class dude).Me, I'm ok with it. I'm willing to do more than my share to help parents out, because I don't want your kids to grow up to be dicks.Saint is not ok with it, and he's expressing that here.
