My cube-mate is considered the most annoying guy in the office. He used to yell "Bless you" when someone in HR sneezed. Note: We do not work in HR. It requires walking through multiple secure doors to get to HR.He says "Bless you my son" if I sneeze. He's jewish. On the one hand, him being jewish is entirely irrelevant. On the other he has a habit of announcing the fact and using it to excuse his exceptionally cheap nature. On the gripping hand he buys tea at Starbucks. He asked me to bring back tea during my visit to Denver. It's $1.50 cheaper in the U.S. I'm not hauling a box of tea through airports & customs so someone can save $1.50 a box on tea. It would have been more likely if he had asked me to pick him up a bottle of booze. (The savings would have been much higher, and the irony(*) would have amused me.).
